  156|     def _reset(self, load):
  157|         """Reset sorted list load factor.
  158| 
  159|         The `load` specifies the load-factor of the list. The default load
  160|         factor of 1000 works well for lists from tens to tens-of-millions of
  161|         values. Good practice is to use a value that is the cube root of the
  162|         list size. With billions of elements, the best load factor depends on
  163|         your usage. It's best to leave the load factor at the default until you
  164|         start benchmarking.
